WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:14.973 --> 00:00:16.308 position:50% align:center
[DEMYNE SHAFT]
Well, well!

00:00:16.391 --> 00:00:18.393 position:50% align:center
If it isn't
Princess Fine herself!

00:00:18.477 --> 00:00:19.811 position:50% align:center
What can I do for you?

00:00:19.895 --> 00:00:21.271 position:50% align:center
Rejoice, Demyne!

00:00:21.355 --> 00:00:23.440 position:50% align:center
It's time to slaughter
those Rekka meatheads

00:00:23.524 --> 00:00:25.442 position:50% align:center
once and for all, we're at war!

00:00:25.526 --> 00:00:27.694 position:50% align:center
[DEMYNE SHAFT] What? But our
Briheight mass production

00:00:27.778 --> 00:00:28.612 position:50% align:center
isn't ready yet--!

00:00:28.695 --> 00:00:30.447 position:50% align:center
One more excuse
and you're dead!

00:00:30.531 --> 00:00:31.615 position:50% align:center
R-Right!

00:00:31.698 --> 00:00:33.659 position:50% align:center
We're gonna use every
weapon we have.

00:00:33.742 --> 00:00:35.452 position:50% align:center
Make sure we're
prepared to fight!

00:00:35.536 --> 00:00:39.248 position:50% align:center
The battle begins at noon
in two days' time!

00:00:39.331 --> 00:00:42.876 position:50% align:center
Huh. Only two days?
Well, sing!

00:00:42.960 --> 00:00:45.629 position:50% align:center
♪ War is drawing nearer ♪

00:00:45.712 --> 00:00:50.509 position:50% align:center
♪ Soon two great nations battle,
choosing their fate ♪

00:00:50.592 --> 00:00:58.016 position:50% align:center
♪ To be the one to rule
them all, all of Lingalind ♪

00:00:58.100 --> 00:01:08.777 position:50% align:center
♪ Oh! It seems the princess
has sealed all our fates! ♪

00:01:09.778 --> 00:01:11.530 position:50% align:center
[PRAX CONRAD]
Princess, I implore you,

00:01:11.613 --> 00:01:13.115 position:50% align:center
please go to your room and rest.

00:01:13.198 --> 00:01:14.658 position:50% align:center
[FINOIR]
You bossin' me around?

00:01:14.741 --> 00:01:17.202 position:50% align:center
[PRAX CONRAD]
Of course not! I serve you.

00:01:17.286 --> 00:01:18.370 position:50% align:center
[FINOIR laughs]

00:01:18.453 --> 00:01:20.038 position:50% align:center
--Oh, shove it!
--[PRAX CONRAD] Princess!

00:01:20.122 --> 00:01:21.498 position:50% align:center
You are so annoying!

00:01:21.582 --> 00:01:25.002 position:50% align:center
Do you need her to
tell you or something?

00:01:25.085 --> 00:01:25.836 position:50% align:center
Prax.

00:01:25.919 --> 00:01:27.087 position:50% align:center
[BOTH gasp]

00:01:27.171 --> 00:01:29.840 position:50% align:center
Princess Fine, please,
try to keep it together!

00:01:29.923 --> 00:01:34.178 position:50% align:center
[FINE FORTEÉ] I'm sorry. I don't
think I can hold her back--

00:01:34.261 --> 00:01:35.762 position:50% align:center
We're about to fight Rekka!

00:01:35.846 --> 00:01:37.514 position:50% align:center
Do you honestly think
we stand a chance

00:01:37.598 --> 00:01:39.725 position:50% align:center
with some flowery wimp
as a Princess?

00:01:39.808 --> 00:01:41.894 position:50% align:center
Get our army ready
to roll immediately!

00:01:41.977 --> 00:01:43.437 position:50% align:center
Got it, 'stache?

00:01:43.520 --> 00:01:46.273 position:50% align:center
[BARAN SUJITA]
Princess, I think--

00:01:46.356 --> 00:01:47.983 position:50% align:center
[FINOIR]
Don't talk back.

00:01:48.066 --> 00:01:51.445 position:50% align:center
It's time to conquer Lingalind.
I don't have time for you.

00:01:51.528 --> 00:01:53.280 position:50% align:center
Uh. Yes.

00:01:53.363 --> 00:02:00.370 position:50% align:center
[FINOIR laughing]

00:02:00.454 --> 00:02:01.997 position:50% align:center
I don't understand what
could have happened

00:02:02.080 --> 00:02:03.665 position:50% align:center
to make her act this way.

00:02:03.749 --> 00:02:06.293 position:50% align:center
She has to know that we're
not prepared for war!

00:02:06.376 --> 00:02:08.086 position:50% align:center
It finally happened.

00:03:44.433 --> 00:03:46.977 position:50% align:center
[SOLDIER A]
Attention, citizens of Lutoh!

00:03:47.060 --> 00:03:51.356 position:50% align:center
In two days, our mighty nation
will go to war with Rekka.

00:03:51.440 --> 00:03:53.192 position:50% align:center
But there's nothing to fear.

00:03:53.275 --> 00:03:55.569 position:50% align:center
The power of our science
cannot be beaten!

00:03:55.652 --> 00:03:57.571 position:50% align:center
We will not let our pride be
broken by the savages of Rekka!

00:03:57.654 --> 00:03:58.947 position:50% align:center
--[MALE A] Really?
--[MALE B] At last!

00:03:59.031 --> 00:04:00.741 position:50% align:center
[FEMALE A] Is this seriously
what the princess wants?

00:04:00.824 --> 00:04:02.743 position:50% align:center
[MALE C] I heard a rumor
she's acting weird.

00:04:02.826 --> 00:04:04.203 position:50% align:center
[FEMALE B]
Yeah, right!

00:04:04.286 --> 00:04:06.038 position:50% align:center
[MALE D] I mean, they'll attack
even if we don't, right?

00:04:06.121 --> 00:04:07.456 position:50% align:center
[MALE E]
Yeah, let's show Rekka!

00:04:07.539 --> 00:04:09.374 position:50% align:center
[MALE F]
I'll help fight, too!

00:04:09.458 --> 00:04:11.001 position:50% align:center
[screaming]

00:04:12.503 --> 00:04:13.545 position:50% align:center
[SOLA ATHIN]
Got some food.

00:04:13.629 --> 00:04:14.671 position:50% align:center
[BIT NAMITAL]
Oh! You're the best!

00:04:14.755 --> 00:04:15.881 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
Thanks.

00:04:15.964 --> 00:04:18.342 position:50% align:center
About Elsha, Atlee,
and the other villagers.

00:04:18.425 --> 00:04:19.593 position:50% align:center
Any idea where they are?

00:04:19.676 --> 00:04:20.844 position:50% align:center
[SOLA ATHIN]
Still in the castle.

00:04:20.928 --> 00:04:23.639 position:50% align:center
Also, Princess Fine's
second personality

00:04:23.722 --> 00:04:25.307 position:50% align:center
is public knowledge now.

00:04:25.390 --> 00:04:27.184 position:50% align:center
They're about to go
to war with Rekka.

00:04:27.267 --> 00:04:28.227 position:50% align:center
Really?

00:04:28.310 --> 00:04:29.770 position:50% align:center
[SHU BI]
So there's lots of bad news.

00:04:29.853 --> 00:04:30.771 position:50% align:center
"Lots of"?

00:04:30.854 --> 00:04:31.897 position:50% align:center
Dare I even say?

00:04:31.980 --> 00:04:33.398 position:50% align:center
Well, hiding it won't help us!

00:04:33.482 --> 00:04:36.276 position:50% align:center
True. Then starting
with number one.

00:04:36.360 --> 00:04:39.071 position:50% align:center
Doctor Sola. Did you
realize you were followed?

00:04:39.154 --> 00:04:40.489 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:04:40.572 --> 00:04:42.199 position:50% align:center
[FRITZ KRAUS]
Found you, Back Arrow!

00:04:42.282 --> 00:04:43.784 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
A lackey of Prax's?

00:04:43.867 --> 00:04:47.913 position:50% align:center
Per my Commander's orders.
I, Fritz Kraus, will slay you!

00:04:47.996 --> 00:04:48.789 position:50% align:center
[FRITZ KRAUS]
Huh?

00:04:48.872 --> 00:04:49.873 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW gasps]

00:04:57.673 --> 00:04:59.424 position:50% align:center
Welcome home, Werner.

00:04:59.508 --> 00:05:01.218 position:50% align:center
[gasps] Dissonanza!

00:05:01.301 --> 00:05:02.678 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
Where's the Briheight?

00:05:02.761 --> 00:05:05.556 position:50% align:center
Oh, don't worry. I just
had him leave, that's all.

00:05:05.639 --> 00:05:06.932 position:50% align:center
[SOLA ATHIN] I don't understand.

00:05:07.015 --> 00:05:08.517 position:50% align:center
You already knew I was back?

00:05:08.600 --> 00:05:10.686 position:50% align:center
[DISSONANZA] Uh-huh! Yup!
I mean, why wouldn't I?

00:05:10.769 --> 00:05:13.188 position:50% align:center
There's nothing in the capital
that "he" doesn't know.

00:05:13.272 --> 00:05:14.273 position:50% align:center
[SHU BI]
Hm?

00:05:14.356 --> 00:05:16.233 position:50% align:center
[SOLA ATHIN gasping]

00:05:16.316 --> 00:05:20.237 position:50% align:center
Now, come with me!
He's eagerly awaiting you.

00:05:23.031 --> 00:05:25.492 position:50% align:center
[SHU BI] Sola. Who's "he"?

00:05:25.576 --> 00:05:28.787 position:50% align:center
[SOLA ATHIN] The worst person
in Lutoh to rub the wrong way,

00:05:28.871 --> 00:05:31.290 position:50% align:center
so let's just do what
we're told for now.

00:05:38.130 --> 00:05:40.507 position:50% align:center
[BIT NAMITAL]
What is this place?

00:05:42.593 --> 00:05:45.053 position:50% align:center
[BIT NAMITAL whimpers]

00:05:54.021 --> 00:05:58.692 position:50% align:center
[chewing]

00:05:58.775 --> 00:06:01.069 position:50% align:center
[RUDOLF CONDUCTORE] Sorry about
eating in front of you.

00:06:01.153 --> 00:06:04.698 position:50% align:center
I don't mean to be rude,
but I can't help it.

00:06:06.700 --> 00:06:07.784 position:50% align:center
Thank you for getting us

00:06:07.868 --> 00:06:10.120 position:50% align:center
out of that dangerous spot,
Elect Supreme.

00:06:10.204 --> 00:06:11.371 position:50% align:center
Elect Supreme?

00:06:11.455 --> 00:06:13.832 position:50% align:center
Oh? Do you know of me?

00:06:13.916 --> 00:06:17.211 position:50% align:center
Through rumors. Though I didn't
think they were actually true.

00:06:17.294 --> 00:06:18.754 position:50% align:center
[RUDOLF CONDUCTORE]
I'd expect the man they call

00:06:18.837 --> 00:06:20.756 position:50% align:center
the "Brains of Rekka"
to know everything,

00:06:20.839 --> 00:06:22.549 position:50% align:center
but I guess
that's not the case.

00:06:22.633 --> 00:06:23.509 position:50% align:center
[SHU BI]
Forgive me.

00:06:23.592 --> 00:06:25.093 position:50% align:center
Who's this guy?

00:06:25.177 --> 00:06:28.847 position:50% align:center
Elect Supreme Rudolf Conductore.
He's one of the Six Supremes,

00:06:28.931 --> 00:06:32.851 position:50% align:center
if you can believe it.
The one who elects the crown.

00:06:32.935 --> 00:06:35.145 position:50% align:center
He decides who
gets the throne?

00:06:35.229 --> 00:06:37.814 position:50% align:center
You mean, he's the most
important guy in the country?

00:06:37.898 --> 00:06:40.275 position:50% align:center
Me? Most important?

00:06:40.359 --> 00:06:41.652 position:50% align:center
Oh crap, he heard me!

00:06:41.735 --> 00:06:44.112 position:50% align:center
[RUDOLF CONDUCTORE]
Such things matter not. Werner?

00:06:44.196 --> 00:06:45.322 position:50% align:center
[SOLA ATHIN]
Yes?

00:06:45.405 --> 00:06:46.740 position:50% align:center
[RUDOLF CONDUCTORE]
I must admit,

00:06:46.823 --> 00:06:48.784 position:50% align:center
you've brought an entertaining
group with you today.

00:06:48.867 --> 00:06:50.536 position:50% align:center
It's important to
have some excitement

00:06:50.619 --> 00:06:53.163 position:50% align:center
every now and then,
so I appreciate it.

00:06:53.247 --> 00:06:56.291 position:50% align:center
Rekka's brains, Lutoh's
former Armored Supreme,

00:06:56.375 --> 00:06:58.210 position:50% align:center
and a man from beyond the wall.

00:06:58.293 --> 00:07:00.963 position:50% align:center
How unusual! [chuckles]

00:07:01.046 --> 00:07:02.923 position:50% align:center
So, Arrow... [belches]

00:07:03.006 --> 00:07:04.341 position:50% align:center
It's my understanding

00:07:04.424 --> 00:07:06.552 position:50% align:center
that you came from
the inside of a Rakuho.

00:07:06.635 --> 00:07:08.303 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
I don't like this.

00:07:08.387 --> 00:07:09.596 position:50% align:center
What are you doing?

00:07:09.680 --> 00:07:11.974 position:50% align:center
I can't remember the first
thing about myself.

00:07:12.057 --> 00:07:13.684 position:50% align:center
But because of that,

00:07:13.767 --> 00:07:16.395 position:50% align:center
I'm a pretty unbiased
judge of character.

00:07:16.478 --> 00:07:18.814 position:50% align:center
Lingalind's an
interesting place so far,

00:07:18.897 --> 00:07:20.899 position:50% align:center
'cause everyone here's
doing their best.

00:07:20.983 --> 00:07:22.776 position:50% align:center
They've got heart,
they have no problem

00:07:22.860 --> 00:07:25.028 position:50% align:center
making their feelings known.

00:07:25.112 --> 00:07:26.530 position:50% align:center
But you're different.

00:07:26.613 --> 00:07:28.866 position:50% align:center
I can't sense your feelings.

00:07:28.949 --> 00:07:32.077 position:50% align:center
How funny. Never would have
pegged you as the smart one.

00:07:32.160 --> 00:07:34.997 position:50% align:center
And I don't like it.

00:07:35.080 --> 00:07:36.874 position:50% align:center
Arrow, move!

00:07:39.418 --> 00:07:41.211 position:50% align:center
[BIT NAMITAL gasping]

00:07:41.295 --> 00:07:44.214 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW groaning]

00:07:46.300 --> 00:07:48.051 position:50% align:center
So much power pours out of me

00:07:48.135 --> 00:07:51.972 position:50% align:center
as soon as I get a little
serious. It's unfortunate.

00:07:52.055 --> 00:07:53.473 position:50% align:center
Was that a Briheight?

00:07:53.557 --> 00:07:56.018 position:50% align:center
They say he has a
Bind Warper inside his body.

00:07:56.101 --> 00:07:57.227 position:50% align:center
Maybe that explains it.

00:07:57.311 --> 00:07:59.897 position:50% align:center
What the hell?

00:07:59.980 --> 00:08:02.566 position:50% align:center
Not even I understand the
true depths of the power

00:08:02.649 --> 00:08:04.651 position:50% align:center
that resides within my body.

00:08:04.735 --> 00:08:07.529 position:50% align:center
Therefore, I immerse myself
in joys and pleasures,

00:08:07.613 --> 00:08:09.072 position:50% align:center
to make it sluggish.

00:08:09.156 --> 00:08:11.158 position:50% align:center
Because if I'm bored
and cumbersome,

00:08:11.241 --> 00:08:13.368 position:50% align:center
I'm able to hold it
back somewhat.

00:08:13.452 --> 00:08:15.787 position:50% align:center
But if I ever got serious
and committed to something,

00:08:15.871 --> 00:08:17.831 position:50% align:center
the world may be destroyed.

00:08:17.915 --> 00:08:20.501 position:50% align:center
Is it that his Bind Warper's
out of control?

00:08:20.584 --> 00:08:22.127 position:50% align:center
Or perhaps it's...

00:08:22.211 --> 00:08:25.714 position:50% align:center
[DISSONANZA] Lord Rudolf,
Secretary Supreme Peath is here.

00:08:25.797 --> 00:08:28.550 position:50% align:center
Uh? You all may stay.

00:08:32.054 --> 00:08:35.140 position:50% align:center
Werner, you've been
through a lot.

00:08:35.224 --> 00:08:37.017 position:50% align:center
Prax told me everything.

00:08:37.100 --> 00:08:38.560 position:50% align:center
Thank you.

00:08:38.644 --> 00:08:40.521 position:50% align:center
[RUDOLF CONDUCTORE] I'm well
aware that Prax is after these

00:08:40.604 --> 00:08:44.399 position:50% align:center
four men, but they're
my guests at the moment.

00:08:44.483 --> 00:08:45.817 position:50% align:center
[PEATH GLINHOUSE]
Yes, sir!

00:08:45.901 --> 00:08:47.986 position:50% align:center
I don't intend to interfere--
go about your business.

00:08:48.070 --> 00:08:49.571 position:50% align:center
[RUDOLF CONDUCTORE]
Hmph. Then why come?

00:08:49.655 --> 00:08:51.657 position:50% align:center
I have news of
the utmost importance.

00:08:51.740 --> 00:08:53.784 position:50% align:center
[RUDOLF CONDUCTORE]
The declaration of war, right?

00:08:53.867 --> 00:08:56.078 position:50% align:center
The "other" Fine commanded it.

00:08:56.161 --> 00:08:57.538 position:50% align:center
You were already aware?

00:08:57.621 --> 00:08:59.081 position:50% align:center
You think I don't
keep tabs on who

00:08:59.164 --> 00:09:00.499 position:50% align:center
I picked for the throne?

00:09:00.582 --> 00:09:02.626 position:50% align:center
I do for all the
possible successors,

00:09:02.709 --> 00:09:05.045 position:50% align:center
as the rest of them
are here to comfort me.

00:09:05.128 --> 00:09:07.589 position:50% align:center
[gasps] Wait, then you mean...

00:09:07.673 --> 00:09:09.967 position:50% align:center
...they're the old
princes and princesses?

00:09:10.050 --> 00:09:12.427 position:50% align:center
[SOLA ATHIN] It's a better fate
than death.

00:09:12.511 --> 00:09:14.429 position:50% align:center
Typically the other
successors would be killed

00:09:14.513 --> 00:09:16.473 position:50% align:center
soon after the selection.

00:09:16.557 --> 00:09:18.892 position:50% align:center
It's to prevent disorder
within the ranks.

00:09:18.976 --> 00:09:20.519 position:50% align:center
But Rudolf pitied them

00:09:20.602 --> 00:09:24.606 position:50% align:center
and decided to make them
his servants instead.

00:09:24.690 --> 00:09:26.024 position:50% align:center
[RUDOLF CONDUCTORE]
When she had the accident,

00:09:26.108 --> 00:09:29.069 position:50% align:center
I gave the princess my blood
in a transfusion.

00:09:29.152 --> 00:09:30.445 position:50% align:center
With how well she handled it,

00:09:30.529 --> 00:09:32.447 position:50% align:center
I thought her a fitting
pick for the crown.

00:09:32.531 --> 00:09:34.575 position:50% align:center
Her resilience
would be an asset.

00:09:34.658 --> 00:09:36.618 position:50% align:center
And yet, here we are.

00:09:36.702 --> 00:09:38.036 position:50% align:center
You gave her your blood?!

00:09:38.120 --> 00:09:39.162 position:50% align:center
You didn't know that?

00:09:39.246 --> 00:09:41.331 position:50% align:center
No. I knew the
surgery was difficult,

00:09:41.415 --> 00:09:43.542 position:50% align:center
but not that Rudolph's
blood was involved.

00:09:43.625 --> 00:09:46.336 position:50% align:center
Hold on! What if it's
all his fault?

00:09:46.420 --> 00:09:48.881 position:50% align:center
She changed after
the accident, right?

00:09:48.964 --> 00:09:50.340 position:50% align:center
[SHU BI]
It's possible.

00:09:50.424 --> 00:09:52.759 position:50% align:center
But why haven't you ever
mentioned this before, Rudolf?!

00:09:52.843 --> 00:09:54.511 position:50% align:center
[RUDOLF CONDUCTORE]
Because nobody asked.

00:09:54.595 --> 00:09:55.971 position:50% align:center
Are you--?

00:09:56.054 --> 00:09:57.055 position:50% align:center
[RUDOLF CONDUCTORE] Put it
this way, if you had known,

00:09:57.139 --> 00:09:58.682 position:50% align:center
what would it change?

00:09:58.765 --> 00:10:00.017 position:50% align:center
[gasping]

00:10:00.100 --> 00:10:03.061 position:50% align:center
I just didn't want Fine to die,
so I took a risk.

00:10:03.145 --> 00:10:04.438 position:50% align:center
[PEATH GLINHOUSE]
Speaking of which,

00:10:04.521 --> 00:10:07.107 position:50% align:center
I'm very sorry to inform you
about your companions.

00:10:07.191 --> 00:10:09.026 position:50% align:center
As in Elsha and the others?

00:10:09.109 --> 00:10:10.861 position:50% align:center
Yes. They can't be helped.

00:10:10.944 --> 00:10:13.197 position:50% align:center
The princess insists
on executing them.

00:10:13.280 --> 00:10:15.324 position:50% align:center
--Execute?
--But why?

00:10:15.407 --> 00:10:16.575 position:50% align:center
[BARAN SUJITA]
Elsha Lean!

00:10:16.658 --> 00:10:18.869 position:50% align:center
You have been chosen to
represent Edger Village

00:10:18.952 --> 00:10:21.121 position:50% align:center
and fight Commander Prax
in a Briheight.

00:10:21.205 --> 00:10:22.748 position:50% align:center
This is not optional.

00:10:22.831 --> 00:10:24.249 position:50% align:center
What the hell is this about?

00:10:24.333 --> 00:10:28.504 position:50% align:center
Isn't it obvious?
I'm after the Granedger, duh!

00:10:28.587 --> 00:10:31.548 position:50% align:center
Don't do it, Elsha!
They'll kill you!

00:10:31.632 --> 00:10:33.509 position:50% align:center
[FINOIR]
We can't exactly help it!

00:10:33.592 --> 00:10:35.177 position:50% align:center
Unless you and
your Briheight die,

00:10:35.260 --> 00:10:37.137 position:50% align:center
nobody else can use the ship!

00:10:37.221 --> 00:10:38.430 position:50% align:center
But once you're good and dead,

00:10:38.514 --> 00:10:40.557 position:50% align:center
we can get a new Briheight
to drive the thing!

00:10:40.641 --> 00:10:42.434 position:50% align:center
One that will do
whatever I tell it to.

00:10:42.518 --> 00:10:44.394 position:50% align:center
You'll kill me to fight Rekka?

00:10:44.478 --> 00:10:46.897 position:50% align:center
You'd put a person to death
just to have a leg up

00:10:46.980 --> 00:10:50.526 position:50% align:center
on your opponent? What happened?
You were all about love before!

00:10:50.609 --> 00:10:52.152 position:50% align:center
Oh, but this is love!

00:10:52.236 --> 00:10:54.655 position:50% align:center
Instead of leaving it in the
hands of you stinky hicks

00:10:54.738 --> 00:10:57.199 position:50% align:center
who have nothing better to do
than tour it around the land,

00:10:57.282 --> 00:11:00.619 position:50% align:center
I'll command Granedger and crush
that damn Rekkan geezer!

00:11:00.702 --> 00:11:02.538 position:50% align:center
That's the love of a ruler!

00:11:02.621 --> 00:11:05.415 position:50% align:center
[ELSHA LEAN] You expect me
to fight and die?

00:11:05.499 --> 00:11:06.667 position:50% align:center
[FINOIR]
Well, if you won't do it,

00:11:06.750 --> 00:11:09.795 position:50% align:center
I'll just kill all
the villagers instead.

00:11:09.878 --> 00:11:12.339 position:50% align:center
That's right! And to make
things more interesting,

00:11:12.422 --> 00:11:14.174 position:50% align:center
we'll start off
with your friend!

00:11:14.258 --> 00:11:16.343 position:50% align:center
Then after that,
we'll kill the old man!

00:11:16.426 --> 00:11:21.473 position:50% align:center
Then the kids.
And so on! [laughs]

00:11:22.683 --> 00:11:23.767 position:50% align:center
[FINOIR]
But here's a thought.

00:11:23.851 --> 00:11:26.061 position:50% align:center
Would you rather
swear loyalty to me?

00:11:26.144 --> 00:11:27.312 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:11:27.396 --> 00:11:28.856 position:50% align:center
[FINOIR] It's not like
your Briheight has to be

00:11:28.939 --> 00:11:31.650 position:50% align:center
fully functional to pilot
Granedger, right?

00:11:31.733 --> 00:11:34.945 position:50% align:center
In that case, we'll just have
your legs chopped off!

00:11:35.028 --> 00:11:37.155 position:50% align:center
We'll just throw your
worthless stump on the ship

00:11:37.239 --> 00:11:39.116 position:50% align:center
and use you when we need to!

00:11:39.199 --> 00:11:40.659 position:50% align:center
So what'll it be?

00:11:40.742 --> 00:11:44.079 position:50% align:center
Lose your legs and sit up on
the prow? Die in this battle?

00:11:44.162 --> 00:11:47.332 position:50% align:center
Or refuse to do either,
and let the villagers die?

00:11:47.416 --> 00:11:50.502 position:50% align:center
Time to decide, Edger girl!

00:12:01.013 --> 00:12:03.640 position:50% align:center
[PEATH GLINHOUSE] Was it wise
to just let them go like that?

00:12:03.724 --> 00:12:06.685 position:50% align:center
Either way, I'm not interested
in causing a scene here.

00:12:06.768 --> 00:12:08.020 position:50% align:center
And if anything happens,

00:12:08.103 --> 00:12:10.564 position:50% align:center
we can always replace the
princess easily enough.

00:12:10.647 --> 00:12:14.067 position:50% align:center
We've got a lot of options,
you see.

00:12:14.151 --> 00:12:15.611 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:12:15.694 --> 00:12:19.489 position:50% align:center
[HANS PALDIN] There you are!
Nobody escapes Hans Paldin!

00:12:19.573 --> 00:12:20.824 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
Give it a rest!

00:12:20.908 --> 00:12:22.951 position:50% align:center
--[BIND WARPER] Manifest armor.
--[GROUP screams]

00:12:26.705 --> 00:12:29.249 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
Huh? You brought friends?

00:12:29.333 --> 00:12:32.669 position:50% align:center
[FINOIR laughs]
What's wrong?

00:12:32.753 --> 00:12:36.882 position:50% align:center
This may come as a shock,
but crying won't help.

00:12:36.965 --> 00:12:38.759 position:50% align:center
[ELSHA LEAN] We were dragged
into this mess,

00:12:38.842 --> 00:12:41.386 position:50% align:center
threatened, nearly killed.

00:12:41.470 --> 00:12:44.765 position:50% align:center
It feels like we're always
at the mercy of other people.

00:12:44.848 --> 00:12:46.350 position:50% align:center
And I'm sick of it!

00:12:46.433 --> 00:12:48.143 position:50% align:center
All right! I'll fight, then!

00:12:48.227 --> 00:12:49.061 position:50% align:center
[laughs]

00:12:49.144 --> 00:12:50.354 position:50% align:center
But on one condition!

00:12:50.437 --> 00:12:52.731 position:50% align:center
You don't think I can win
anyway, so if I do,

00:12:52.814 --> 00:12:54.566 position:50% align:center
I want you to
release the villagers!

00:12:54.650 --> 00:12:56.652 position:50% align:center
[FINOIR]
The idiot's making demands now.

00:12:56.735 --> 00:12:59.696 position:50% align:center
[ELSHA LEAN] I'm Edger's chief.
Don't be so condescending.

00:12:59.780 --> 00:13:01.990 position:50% align:center
Nobody tells me what to do!

00:13:02.074 --> 00:13:03.283 position:50% align:center
--[PRAX CONRAD] Princess!
--[FINOIR] Huh?

00:13:03.367 --> 00:13:05.118 position:50% align:center
I think it makes
things interesting.

00:13:05.202 --> 00:13:07.246 position:50% align:center
Why don't we accept
her proposal?

00:13:07.329 --> 00:13:08.413 position:50% align:center
[FINOIR]
Hm?

00:13:08.497 --> 00:13:09.831 position:50% align:center
[PRAX CONRAD]
If we allow her some hope,

00:13:09.915 --> 00:13:12.584 position:50% align:center
she'll cling to it and
die with it unfulfilled.

00:13:12.668 --> 00:13:14.837 position:50% align:center
I can't think of a more
fitting end for an idiot

00:13:14.920 --> 00:13:17.172 position:50% align:center
who defies our
glorious princess.

00:13:17.256 --> 00:13:21.343 position:50% align:center
Huh. Not like Prax'll lose
anyway, what do I care?

00:13:21.426 --> 00:13:22.636 position:50% align:center
Very well.

00:13:22.719 --> 00:13:25.013 position:50% align:center
If you can pull out a win,
I'll do as you wish!

00:13:25.097 --> 00:13:28.100 position:50% align:center
[sighs] Shall we get started?

00:13:28.183 --> 00:13:31.144 position:50% align:center
Yeah. I know I don't
stand much of a chance,

00:13:31.228 --> 00:13:34.231 position:50% align:center
but I'm not about to throw away
my life without even trying.

00:13:34.314 --> 00:13:35.816 position:50% align:center
[BIND WARPER]
Manifest Armor.

00:13:35.899 --> 00:13:39.403 position:50% align:center
[PRAX CONRAD] I'm the Armored
Supreme of Lutoh, Prax Conrad!

00:13:39.486 --> 00:13:41.905 position:50% align:center
[ELSHA LEAN] I'm Edger Village's
chief, Elsha Lean!

00:13:41.989 --> 00:13:44.241 position:50% align:center
And I'll show you
I've got backbone, too!

00:13:44.324 --> 00:13:45.492 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasping]

00:13:45.576 --> 00:13:46.952 position:50% align:center
Do you think she can win?

00:13:47.035 --> 00:13:48.036 position:50% align:center
[PRAX CONRAD]
Don't think ill of me!

00:13:48.120 --> 00:13:49.413 position:50% align:center
Bring it!

00:13:51.999 --> 00:13:54.877 position:50% align:center
[PRAX CONRAD]
Ha. So where's that backbone?

00:13:54.960 --> 00:13:57.004 position:50% align:center
Turns out you're just inelegant!

00:13:57.087 --> 00:14:00.424 position:50% align:center
[ELSHA LEAN] So what? I've still
been training to fight!

00:14:00.507 --> 00:14:02.634 position:50% align:center
[PRAX CONRAD]
Ha! Not too bad, kid!

00:14:02.718 --> 00:14:04.094 position:50% align:center
[ELSHA LEAN]
Don't belittle me!

00:14:04.178 --> 00:14:06.972 position:50% align:center
[PRAX CONRAD] That won't be
enough to win, Elsha Lean!

00:14:07.055 --> 00:14:08.348 position:50% align:center
[ELSHA LEAN screaming]

00:14:08.432 --> 00:14:09.433 position:50% align:center
[BURK LEAN]
Elsha!

00:14:09.516 --> 00:14:11.143 position:50% align:center
Outta the way!

00:14:12.769 --> 00:14:13.520 position:50% align:center
[FRITZ KRAUS gasps]

00:14:13.604 --> 00:14:15.063 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
Heh... Uh?!

00:14:15.147 --> 00:14:16.648 position:50% align:center
You think you can run from us?

00:14:16.732 --> 00:14:18.066 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW grunts]

00:14:18.150 --> 00:14:20.235 position:50% align:center
[HANS PALDIN] We've been
personally trained by Prax!

00:14:20.319 --> 00:14:22.779 position:50% align:center
The Armored Division
can take care of you!

00:14:22.863 --> 00:14:24.781 position:50% align:center
Yeah, when it's five on one!

00:14:24.865 --> 00:14:27.534 position:50% align:center
And as we've discovered,
he can't clone with us in here.

00:14:27.618 --> 00:14:28.994 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
What the hell?

00:14:29.077 --> 00:14:31.413 position:50% align:center
What kind of guy am I if I
can't even save my friends?

00:14:31.496 --> 00:14:32.998 position:50% align:center
I'm stuck dealing
with these jerks

00:14:33.081 --> 00:14:34.917 position:50% align:center
when time is of the essence!

00:14:35.000 --> 00:14:37.544 position:50% align:center
Come on. I just gotta
make it to them, right?

00:14:37.628 --> 00:14:39.963 position:50% align:center
So basically, I need...

00:14:40.047 --> 00:14:41.089 position:50% align:center
For loyalty!

00:14:41.173 --> 00:14:43.342 position:50% align:center
[FRITZ KRAUS]
Farewell, Back Arrow!

00:14:43.425 --> 00:14:46.428 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
Something to get me there!

00:14:46.512 --> 00:14:50.682 position:50% align:center
[yelling]

00:14:50.766 --> 00:14:51.767 position:50% align:center
[HANS PALDIN]
What the--?

00:14:51.850 --> 00:14:53.977 position:50% align:center
[FRITZ KRAUS]
Wait, what's he doing?

00:14:54.061 --> 00:14:57.814 position:50% align:center
Yeah. Flying'll work well!

00:14:57.898 --> 00:14:59.399 position:50% align:center
[HANS PALDIN]
S-Seriously?

00:14:59.483 --> 00:15:03.362 position:50% align:center
[FRITZ KRAUS] How can he just do
that? Not even we can fly yet!

00:15:04.655 --> 00:15:05.989 position:50% align:center
It's like a new Muga!

00:15:06.073 --> 00:15:09.618 position:50% align:center
No one but Arrow could
pull of something this crazy!

00:15:10.744 --> 00:15:12.704 position:50% align:center
[ELSHA LEAN grunting]

00:15:12.788 --> 00:15:14.665 position:50% align:center
Huh. Impressive block.

00:15:14.748 --> 00:15:16.041 position:50% align:center
So patronizing!

00:15:16.124 --> 00:15:19.336 position:50% align:center
Yeah, you're a noble
and she's a princess.

00:15:19.419 --> 00:15:20.629 position:50% align:center
But if you think that means

00:15:20.712 --> 00:15:23.131 position:50% align:center
you're always gonna get
your way, you're wrong!

00:15:23.215 --> 00:15:26.176 position:50% align:center
Why are you struggling?
Finish her already!

00:15:26.260 --> 00:15:27.386 position:50% align:center
[PRAX CONRAD]
Right away!

00:15:27.469 --> 00:15:28.762 position:50% align:center
[ELSHA LEAN groans]

00:15:28.846 --> 00:15:30.472 position:50% align:center
[PRAX CONRAD] To think you'd
make me resort to this.

00:15:30.556 --> 00:15:32.933 position:50% align:center
No matter... It'll end you!

00:15:33.016 --> 00:15:35.853 position:50% align:center
--[BACK ARROW yells]
--[PRAX CONRAD gasps]

00:15:35.936 --> 00:15:37.688 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW] You bastards
don't get to kill Elsha

00:15:37.771 --> 00:15:39.439 position:50% align:center
just 'cause you feel
like it, all right?

00:15:39.523 --> 00:15:40.607 position:50% align:center
Arrow!

00:15:40.691 --> 00:15:42.818 position:50% align:center
He's not falling.
Is he flying somehow?

00:15:42.901 --> 00:15:44.319 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
Sorry, I'm late!

00:15:44.403 --> 00:15:45.821 position:50% align:center
I'm here, too!
What're you doing?

00:15:45.904 --> 00:15:49.324 position:50% align:center
And how does letting everyone
know that help us at all?

00:15:49.408 --> 00:15:50.325 position:50% align:center
[PRAX CONRAD]
Fascinating.

00:15:50.409 --> 00:15:52.077 position:50% align:center
I never would have
expected this.

00:15:52.160 --> 00:15:54.037 position:50% align:center
You've learned to fly
all on your own.

00:15:54.121 --> 00:15:55.247 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
Sure did!

00:15:55.330 --> 00:15:57.457 position:50% align:center
Now I think it's time
to finish our fight!

00:15:57.541 --> 00:15:59.751 position:50% align:center
--[ELSHA LEAN] Wait, Arrow!
--[BACK ARROW] Huh?

00:15:59.835 --> 00:16:02.296 position:50% align:center
[ELSHA LEAN] I'll fight Prax
on my own. Stand back!

00:16:02.379 --> 00:16:03.380 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:16:03.463 --> 00:16:05.382 position:50% align:center
I can't have you
taking over and winning.

00:16:05.465 --> 00:16:07.843 position:50% align:center
Princess Fine made a promise
to free the villagers

00:16:07.926 --> 00:16:10.804 position:50% align:center
if I defeat Prax,
not if you do, okay?

00:16:10.888 --> 00:16:13.432 position:50% align:center
Stop, Elsha!
You know you can't win!

00:16:13.515 --> 00:16:16.226 position:50% align:center
[ELSHA LEAN]
I will win, because I have to.

00:16:16.310 --> 00:16:18.353 position:50% align:center
[PRAX CONRAD] You've got guts,
I'll give you that,

00:16:18.437 --> 00:16:20.522 position:50% align:center
but you need to know
your own limits.

00:16:20.606 --> 00:16:22.524 position:50% align:center
I didn't ask for your opinion!

00:16:22.608 --> 00:16:24.151 position:50% align:center
Prax, this is stupid.

00:16:24.234 --> 00:16:26.403 position:50% align:center
Hurry up and finish
your food, will you?

00:16:26.486 --> 00:16:28.488 position:50% align:center
Then for dessert, capture Arrow.

00:16:28.572 --> 00:16:30.824 position:50% align:center
Good luck with that.
As long as I've known her,

00:16:30.908 --> 00:16:33.577 position:50% align:center
Edger's leader's been tough
as hell! Isn't that right?

00:16:33.660 --> 00:16:35.579 position:50% align:center
By the way, I'm sorry
about ditching you guys

00:16:35.662 --> 00:16:37.706 position:50% align:center
for the wall, I really
shouldn't have done that.

00:16:37.789 --> 00:16:39.833 position:50% align:center
[ELSHA LEAN]
Hell of a time for an apology.

00:16:39.917 --> 00:16:44.713 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW] This is to
make up for it! Elsha! Use me!

00:16:44.796 --> 00:16:46.673 position:50% align:center
[ELSHA LEAN gasps]

00:16:46.757 --> 00:16:48.258 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
I told you once before,

00:16:48.342 --> 00:16:51.136 position:50% align:center
"the only one who can really
save you is yourself.

00:16:51.220 --> 00:16:55.766 position:50% align:center
But I think I can
probably help you out!"

00:16:55.849 --> 00:16:57.309 position:50% align:center
I can be your sword!

00:16:57.392 --> 00:16:59.144 position:50% align:center
Pick me up and cut down the wall

00:16:59.228 --> 00:17:02.481 position:50% align:center
that's standing in
the way of your destiny!

00:17:02.564 --> 00:17:04.316 position:50% align:center
All right.

00:17:06.902 --> 00:17:09.154 position:50% align:center
I'm confused, did he
change shape this time?

00:17:09.238 --> 00:17:11.990 position:50% align:center
How wonderfully unexpected!
I'm not complaining!

00:17:12.074 --> 00:17:13.492 position:50% align:center
This is bullshit!

00:17:13.575 --> 00:17:15.702 position:50% align:center
Go kill the captives,
kids and all!

00:17:15.786 --> 00:17:17.079 position:50% align:center
[VILLAGERS whimpering]

00:17:17.162 --> 00:17:20.165 position:50% align:center
Please stop it, Princess!
This is a knight's duel!

00:17:20.249 --> 00:17:22.918 position:50% align:center
I ask that you do not
sully my honor like this.

00:17:23.001 --> 00:17:25.170 position:50% align:center
Prax!

00:17:25.254 --> 00:17:27.464 position:50% align:center
Elsha, let's do this elegantly.

00:17:27.548 --> 00:17:31.009 position:50% align:center
[ELSHA LEAN]
Y-Yeah!

00:17:31.093 --> 00:17:32.219 position:50% align:center
[PRAX CONRAD]
Once again.

00:17:32.302 --> 00:17:35.597 position:50% align:center
I'm the Armored Supreme
of Lutoh, Prax Conrad!

00:17:35.681 --> 00:17:38.433 position:50% align:center
[ELSHA LEAN grunting]
I'm Edger Village's chief,

00:17:38.517 --> 00:17:41.478 position:50% align:center
Elsha Lean!

00:17:45.148 --> 00:17:46.567 position:50% align:center
[PRAX CONRAD]
Wide open!

00:17:46.650 --> 00:17:48.151 position:50% align:center
Arrow, you're too heavy!

00:17:48.235 --> 00:17:50.404 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
Sorry! These guys weigh me down!

00:17:50.487 --> 00:17:51.321 position:50% align:center
[PRAX CONRAD]
You're mine!

00:17:51.405 --> 00:17:55.951 position:50% align:center
I'm not gonna lose to you!

00:17:56.034 --> 00:17:57.578 position:50% align:center
She sped up?

00:17:57.661 --> 00:18:00.080 position:50% align:center
Still, you're open
to attack from above!

00:18:00.163 --> 00:18:01.748 position:50% align:center
[VILLAGERS gasping]

00:18:01.832 --> 00:18:03.625 position:50% align:center
[ELSHA LEAN]
I'll win my freedom...

00:18:03.709 --> 00:18:05.252 position:50% align:center
Do it!

00:18:07.421 --> 00:18:10.132 position:50% align:center
...by exploiting your oversight!

00:18:10.215 --> 00:18:11.300 position:50% align:center
What?

00:18:11.383 --> 00:18:14.052 position:50% align:center
[ELSHA LEAN]
I'll slice you in two!

00:18:19.725 --> 00:18:21.852 position:50% align:center
[gasping]

00:18:21.935 --> 00:18:24.313 position:50% align:center
[PRAX CONRAD]
I-Impressive...

00:18:25.397 --> 00:18:29.193 position:50% align:center
Prax! No, you'll die!

00:18:35.824 --> 00:18:37.618 position:50% align:center
You should consider
yourself lucky.

00:18:37.701 --> 00:18:40.454 position:50% align:center
Since Muga sliced you,
you lost without dying.

00:18:40.537 --> 00:18:42.706 position:50% align:center
I had heard whispers about that.

00:18:42.789 --> 00:18:44.333 position:50% align:center
It's an incredible power.

00:18:44.416 --> 00:18:47.461 position:50% align:center
[FINE FORTEÉ]
Prax! Thank goodness!

00:18:47.544 --> 00:18:49.588 position:50% align:center
Are you back to
your usual self?

00:18:49.671 --> 00:18:51.006 position:50% align:center
Uh-huh.

00:18:51.089 --> 00:18:54.510 position:50% align:center
You're a joke, Prax. Guess what?
I'm gonna kill you, too!

00:18:54.593 --> 00:18:55.844 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:18:55.928 --> 00:18:58.096 position:50% align:center
[FINOIR] Bring a Bind Warper!
I'll do it myself!

00:18:58.180 --> 00:18:59.848 position:50% align:center
[ELSHA LEAN]
Hey, what about your promise?

00:18:59.932 --> 00:19:02.434 position:50% align:center
[FINOIR]
You think I care about that?

00:19:02.518 --> 00:19:05.395 position:50% align:center
Princess. I implore you,
get a hold of yourself!

00:19:05.479 --> 00:19:07.439 position:50% align:center
We've recently learned
that during your surgery,

00:19:07.523 --> 00:19:09.733 position:50% align:center
you were given Elect
Supreme Rudolf's Blood!

00:19:09.816 --> 00:19:10.943 position:50% align:center
Your split personality may--

00:19:11.026 --> 00:19:14.613 position:50% align:center
[PRAX CONRAD]
What? She was? Is that true?

00:19:14.696 --> 00:19:17.282 position:50% align:center
It is.
Rudolf told us so himself.

00:19:17.366 --> 00:19:18.700 position:50% align:center
[PRAX CONRAD gasping]

00:19:18.784 --> 00:19:20.911 position:50% align:center
[ELSHA LEAN] Princess Fine,
when we first met,

00:19:20.994 --> 00:19:22.579 position:50% align:center
you preached to us about love.

00:19:22.663 --> 00:19:25.165 position:50% align:center
I know that was the
true you speaking!

00:19:25.249 --> 00:19:26.708 position:50% align:center
I just won my fight,

00:19:26.792 --> 00:19:28.669 position:50% align:center
now it's your turn
to do the same!

00:19:28.752 --> 00:19:31.880 position:50% align:center
Use your love to slay
the evil buried inside you!

00:19:31.964 --> 00:19:35.300 position:50% align:center
[FINOIR] Shut up! Shut up!
Shut up! Shut up already!

00:19:35.384 --> 00:19:37.094 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:19:37.177 --> 00:19:39.263 position:50% align:center
Open your eyes, Fine Forté!

00:19:39.346 --> 00:19:40.597 position:50% align:center
I said shut up!

00:19:40.681 --> 00:19:43.267 position:50% align:center
I'm gonna destroy
every one of you!

00:19:43.350 --> 00:19:46.854 position:50% align:center
I'll slaughter you all
with my Briheight!

00:19:46.937 --> 00:19:49.565 position:50% align:center
No. I've made my
decision, it's over.

00:19:49.648 --> 00:19:50.816 position:50% align:center
Huh? You what?

00:19:50.899 --> 00:19:52.860 position:50% align:center
[FINE FORTEÉ]
I was afraid.

00:19:52.943 --> 00:19:57.322 position:50% align:center
Of you, and of war,
but mostly myself.

00:19:57.406 --> 00:19:59.783 position:50% align:center
That's why I've always
hidden in your shadow,

00:19:59.867 --> 00:20:01.368 position:50% align:center
but now I know!

00:20:01.451 --> 00:20:03.662 position:50% align:center
I can accept you as a part of me

00:20:03.745 --> 00:20:07.666 position:50% align:center
and shoulder all the blood
spilled because of my actions.

00:20:07.749 --> 00:20:10.836 position:50% align:center
And what's more,
I'll love everything!

00:20:10.919 --> 00:20:13.463 position:50% align:center
I'll pursue a world
full of love!

00:20:13.547 --> 00:20:15.257 position:50% align:center
[FINOIR]
Stop it!

00:20:15.340 --> 00:20:18.760 position:50% align:center
From this moment forward,
I'll be taking charge!

00:20:18.844 --> 00:20:22.264 position:50% align:center
It's time for you to rest.

00:20:22.347 --> 00:20:25.267 position:50% align:center
[screaming]

00:20:38.155 --> 00:20:40.782 position:50% align:center
I'm terribly sorry for the
trouble I've caused you all.

00:20:40.866 --> 00:20:42.367 position:50% align:center
Especially Elsha.

00:20:42.451 --> 00:20:45.746 position:50% align:center
I apologize for how cruel
and rude I've been to you.

00:20:45.829 --> 00:20:47.247 position:50% align:center
Uh, yeah.

00:20:47.331 --> 00:20:49.958 position:50% align:center
Did the Bind Warper somehow
seal her other personality?

00:20:50.042 --> 00:20:51.835 position:50% align:center
For real? Can they do that?

00:20:51.919 --> 00:20:52.836 position:50% align:center
Maybe.

00:20:52.920 --> 00:20:53.962 position:50% align:center
"Maybe"?

00:20:54.046 --> 00:20:56.215 position:50% align:center
Credit where
credit's due, Princess.

00:20:56.298 --> 00:21:00.260 position:50% align:center
[TOM] Hey, Arrow!
Is everyone safe now?

00:21:00.344 --> 00:21:01.637 position:50% align:center
[BACK ARROW]
Yeah, you're fine!

00:21:01.720 --> 00:21:03.722 position:50% align:center
[ANNIE]
Yay!

00:21:03.805 --> 00:21:05.224 position:50% align:center
[exhales]

00:21:05.307 --> 00:21:13.607 position:50% align:center
[RUDOLF CONDUCTORE laughing]

00:21:14.650 --> 00:21:16.109 position:50% align:center
[FINE FORTEÉ]
I'm very sorry.

00:21:16.193 --> 00:21:20.781 position:50% align:center
I tried my best, but it seems
we can't avoid going to war.

00:21:20.864 --> 00:21:22.741 position:50% align:center
It is all my fault.

00:21:22.824 --> 00:21:25.953 position:50% align:center
I suggest you leave so you
don't get dragged into it.

00:21:26.036 --> 00:21:27.746 position:50% align:center
It's not your problem.

00:21:27.829 --> 00:21:30.958 position:50% align:center
Excuse me, but what do you
fight for, Princess Fine?

00:21:31.041 --> 00:21:32.334 position:50% align:center
Only to protect our nation

00:21:32.417 --> 00:21:34.795 position:50% align:center
from the Republic
of Rekka's advances.

00:21:34.878 --> 00:21:37.506 position:50% align:center
I'm sure the sacrifice
is going to be tremendous,

00:21:37.589 --> 00:21:40.425 position:50% align:center
but I will take full
responsibility for it.

00:21:40.509 --> 00:21:41.760 position:50% align:center
[ELSHA LEAN]
Good answer.

00:21:41.844 --> 00:21:44.471 position:50% align:center
I'll help you out, as
a fellow leader, that is.

00:21:44.555 --> 00:21:45.681 position:50% align:center
[FINE FORTEÉ]
What?

00:21:45.764 --> 00:21:47.891 position:50% align:center
[ELSHA LEAN] I mean,
Rekka's after us anyway.

00:21:47.975 --> 00:21:50.519 position:50% align:center
Plus, trust is met with trust.

00:21:50.602 --> 00:21:52.688 position:50% align:center
That's the Edger way.

00:21:57.693 --> 00:22:00.237 position:50% align:center
What would you say to forming
an alliance, Princess?

00:22:00.320 --> 00:22:02.739 position:50% align:center
I'd say, "thank you," Elsha!